ğŸ PASSO 2 â€” Script Nmap â€œversÃ£o portfÃ³lioâ€

Vamos melhorar aquele script simples e deixar executÃ¡vel + reutilizÃ¡vel.

ğŸ“„ scans/nmap_scan.py

import subprocess
import sys

def run_nmap(target):
    print(f"[+] Iniciando varredura Nmap em {target}...\n")
    command = ["nmap", "-sV", target]
    result = subprocess.run(command, capture_output=True, text=True)

    if result.stdout:
        print(result.stdout)

    if result.stderr:
        print("[!] Erro durante a execuÃ§Ã£o do Nmap")
        print(result.stderr)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    if len(sys.argv) != 2:
        print("Uso: python nmap_scan.py <alvo>")
        sys.exit(1)

    run_nmap(sys.argv[1])


ğŸ“Œ ExecuÃ§Ã£o:

python scans/nmap_scan.py 192.168.56.124


ğŸ‘‰ Tire print do terminal depois disso (vai pro prints/).

ğŸ§  PASSO 3 â€” Threat Intelligence separada

ğŸ“„ threat_intel/cve_collector.py

import requests

def get_latest_cves(limit=5):
    url = "https://cve.circl.lu/api/last"
    response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)

    if response.status_code != 200:
        print("Erro ao acessar API de CVEs")
        return

    data = response.json()[:limit]

    print("[+] Ãšltimas vulnerabilidades publicadas:\n")
    for cve in data:
        print(f"- {cve['id']}: {cve['summary'][:100]}...")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    get_latest_cves()


ğŸ“Œ ExecuÃ§Ã£o:

python threat_intel/cve_collector.py


